   Conclusion: Patients with septic shock are complicated with disordered expressions of inflammatory factors. During resuscitation, Ringer's sodium pyruvate solution can effectively promote blood circulation, mitigate inflammation and maintain acid-base equilibrium, thus decreasing the prognostic mortality rate.
